verse_part: Otherwise it shall come to pass,
And when he was come in
and I was delivered of a child
were about him on every side,
and will cause them to be discharged
from one side of the floor
so that they carry them away
of them that carried them captives,
that they may have compassion on them:
she shall feign herself [to be] another
and the things which himself had dedicated,
as if it had been a light thing
And it shall come to pass,
And they did [it] the second time.
And they did [it] the third time.
And it came to pass in the mean while,
And it shall come to pass,
as he that putteth it off.
whether [any thing would come] from him,
and he caused him to come up
as soon as thou art departed
And as soon as he was departed
whom I appointed to utter destruction,
and him that is shut up
unto the driver of his chariot,
